WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:32.008 --> 01:35.052
[ Motorcycle passing ]

01:38.807 --> 01:41.558
As far as I can see, these guys
are completely legit, Danny.

01:42.060 --> 01:43.185
The bank has checked them out,

01:43.394 --> 01:44.520
they're just as convinced
as I am,

01:44.729 --> 01:46.063
and they're willing to go
all the way with us.

01:46.397 --> 01:48.565
You know, the idea
of a franchised operation

01:48.775 --> 01:50.984
for plastic surgery resorts
is a natural.

01:51.194 --> 01:53.946
It's one of those magnificent,
inevitable ideas.

01:54.155 --> 01:55.322
Banks are always quick
to say that

01:55.532 --> 01:56.782
when everything's rolling easy.

01:57.784 --> 01:58.784
But you take it from me,

01:59.035 --> 02:01.245
the first signs of heat
from the Medical Association,

02:01.454 --> 02:03.288
the first cries
of professional outrage,

02:03.623 --> 02:04.748
the bank will call back its note

02:04.958 --> 02:06.166
and leave us hanging
by our thumbs.

02:06.376 --> 02:08.877
It's not the financing
that's bothering you, Dan.

02:09.294 --> 02:11.088
Your voice has that edge to it.

02:11.506 --> 02:12.923
I never denied it.

02:13.842 --> 02:16.176
I just sure as hell don't want
to become the Colonel Sanders

02:16.386 --> 02:17.261
of plastic surgery.

02:17.470 --> 02:18.720
[ Chuckles ]
Why not?

02:19.055 --> 02:20.264
Sounds great to me.

02:56.301 --> 02:57.593
WOMAN: We passed it.

02:57.802 --> 02:59.887
MAN: We didn't pass it.
I remember that farm.

03:00.096 --> 03:01.305
WOMAN: We passed it.

03:01.639 --> 03:04.057
That farm is past
concession road 12.

03:04.559 --> 03:07.102
We were supposed to turn
on concession road 11.

03:07.312 --> 03:09.354
I don't remember that farm, Dad.

03:09.647 --> 03:10.647
We didn't pass it.

03:10.857 --> 03:13.150
I very distinctly
remember that farm!

03:13.610 --> 03:15.485
If you would just
stop this vehicle

03:15.695 --> 03:17.154
long enough to look
at this map,

03:17.363 --> 03:18.447
-I will show you...
-All right!

03:18.656 --> 03:20.157
WOMAN: ...beyond a
shadow of a...

03:20.366 --> 03:23.160
MAN: You are both right,
and I'm all wrong.

03:24.204 --> 03:25.662
We'll turn around
and go all the way back.

03:35.048 --> 03:37.007
-[ Engine sputtering ]
-Goddamn thing.

03:41.971 --> 03:42.679
[ Engine sputtering ]

03:42.889 --> 03:44.473
Shoulda never sold
the station wagon.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.643
-Christ, Bob.
-Hm? Oh, Christ!

03:48.186 --> 03:50.020
[ Tires screeching ]

03:54.108 --> 03:56.109
[ Engine revving ]

03:57.820 --> 03:58.612
[ Gasping ]

03:58.947 --> 03:59.905
[ Screams ]

04:05.245 --> 04:05.994
Lloyd!

04:06.663 --> 04:07.412
Lloyd!

04:07.622 --> 04:11.541
My God! I just saw a motorcycle
explode in that field!

04:12.210 --> 04:14.253
[ Gasping ]

04:17.882 --> 04:20.050
My God, I think there's someone
trapped under it.

04:20.510 --> 04:22.010
I better tell the boys inside.

04:24.847 --> 04:25.764
[ Phone beeping ]

04:26.307 --> 04:27.808
<i>MAN: Is Dr. Keloid there?</i>
<i>It's urgent.</i>

04:28.726 --> 04:29.726
Yeah, what is it, Steve?

04:29.936 --> 04:30.852
<i>STEVE: There's been</i>
<i>a motorcycle accident</i>

04:31.062 --> 04:32.145
<i>a few minutes</i>
<i>down the highway.</i>

04:32.397 --> 04:33.814
<i>Should I take the ambulance</i>
<i>and go get 'em?</i>

04:34.482 --> 04:35.357
Yeah, sure.

04:35.650 --> 04:37.067
<i>MAN: What am I supposed to do?</i>

04:37.277 --> 04:38.735
<i>Go back to three of the largest</i>
<i>investment groups</i>

04:38.945 --> 04:39.945
<i>in North America and say...</i>

04:40.196 --> 04:42.406
-Steve? Are you still there?
<i>-STEVE: Yep.</i>

04:42.699 --> 04:44.366
Well, hang on a minute.
I'm comin' right with ya.

04:44.575 --> 04:45.325
I'll meet you out front.

04:45.535 --> 04:48.287
Now, Dan. We have a lot
of important decisions to make.

04:48.496 --> 04:50.163
Well, you and Murray
work it out between you, hon.

04:50.415 --> 04:52.416
Just make the pill easy
for me to swallow.

04:54.836 --> 04:56.420
Well, don't look at me.
You married him.

04:56.629 --> 04:58.297
Bob, get back!

04:58.715 --> 05:01.466
Bob! Be careful, Bob!

05:01.676 --> 05:03.927
Get him back!
Hold him back there!

05:14.314 --> 05:16.064
Get the flasher on and let's go.

05:16.649 --> 05:19.067
[ Siren wails ]

05:50.183 --> 05:51.391
WOMAN: One of them's
under the bike.

05:51.601 --> 05:53.143
There's another one over there.

06:00.568 --> 06:02.069
[ Whispers ]
Oh, my God.

06:02.445 --> 06:04.821
-[ Siren wailing ]
-How's her bleeding?

06:05.365 --> 06:06.198
Heavy.

06:07.825 --> 06:11.161
The man's got a broken hand,
separated shoulder, concussion.

06:11.496 --> 06:12.704
We can send him to the General.

06:12.914 --> 06:14.956
But it's definitely
major surgery for her,

06:15.166 --> 06:15.749
and right now.

06:16.501 --> 06:18.877
I know we're not,
but we've got no choice.

06:20.338 --> 06:22.589
-How's her blood pressure?
-Steady.

06:22.924 --> 06:24.591
I'd say she's got
a half an hour to live,

06:24.801 --> 06:26.843
and it's three hours
to the nearest serious hospital.

06:27.220 --> 06:28.929
Look, it's us or nobody.

06:29.514 --> 06:31.848
[ Siren wailing ]

06:32.558 --> 06:34.601
[ Indistinct chatter ]

06:36.104 --> 06:37.604
It must be bad.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.875
MAN: Come on, come on, come on!
Move! Move! Move it!

06:59.085 --> 07:00.419
Oh, my God.

07:01.921 --> 07:03.505
Get it-- get it up!

07:05.258 --> 07:06.675
Come on, move it.
We don't want to lose her.

07:07.093 --> 07:07.884
The guy in the van,

07:08.553 --> 07:10.929
he's got a concussion,
separated shoulder, broken hand.

07:11.472 --> 07:13.265
Maybe some Demerol
if he becomes lucid.

07:13.558 --> 07:15.225
WOMAN: Okay, Dr. Keloid.

07:28.823 --> 07:30.949
Okay, boys. Let's take her
right into pre-op.

07:31.534 --> 07:32.784
Has Dr. Karl set her up
for the works?

07:32.994 --> 07:34.453
NURSE: We're ready to go,
Doctor.

07:35.955 --> 07:36.997
What's that all about?

07:37.248 --> 07:38.957
Somebody said something
about an accident.

07:39.834 --> 07:42.419
You'd think they could cover it
with a sheet or something.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.671
I don't buy it, Dan.

07:45.631 --> 07:46.840
You haven't seen her.

07:47.216 --> 07:48.967
I don't have to see her.

07:49.510 --> 07:52.220
Neutral field grafts
have never been used internally.

07:52.555 --> 07:55.474
We could end up with a terminal
cancer patient on our hands.

07:55.683 --> 07:57.601
Aw, come on.
We can monitor, Roxy.

07:58.019 --> 08:00.145
She's got nothing to lose.
Literally.

08:02.106 --> 08:02.898
[ Sighs ]

08:04.066 --> 08:06.234
So, listen, when do I
get to see Rose?

08:07.653 --> 08:09.070
NURSE: Not for a while.

08:10.281 --> 08:11.448
Why not?

08:18.080 --> 08:19.748
Oh, Jesus!

08:22.752 --> 08:24.169
I didn't kill her, did I?

08:25.838 --> 08:27.047
She's not dead.

08:28.341 --> 08:29.591
[ Sighs ]

08:38.726 --> 08:40.393
Now, I know everyone here
is familiar

08:40.602 --> 08:42.645
with standard techniques
of skin grafting.

08:43.022 --> 08:45.398
But what we're going to do
is a little out of the ordinary.

08:45.650 --> 08:47.108
I'll explain as we go along.

08:47.735 --> 08:50.570
We're removing full thickness
thigh material

08:50.780 --> 08:52.030
from the patient's thighs,

08:52.240 --> 08:54.783
as per normal graft
acquisition procedure.

08:54.992 --> 08:55.742
However,

08:55.952 --> 08:58.870
before applying the grafts
to the damaged areas

08:59.080 --> 09:01.456
of the patient's breasts,
abdomen, and so on,

09:01.958 --> 09:03.041
we're going to treat them

09:03.251 --> 09:05.752
so that they become
morphogenetically neutral.

09:07.755 --> 09:09.965
They will then be called
neutral field grafts.

09:10.299 --> 09:11.967
[ Dermatome whirring ]

09:12.677 --> 09:14.844
Well, when the thigh skin tissue
is treated,

09:15.054 --> 09:16.471
it'll lose its specificity,

09:17.056 --> 09:20.100
as both thigh tissue
and skin tissue.

09:21.602 --> 09:22.686
For example,

09:24.355 --> 09:26.398
if it were grafted
to a burned cheek,

09:26.857 --> 09:28.108
it wouldn't just be thigh skin,

09:28.317 --> 09:29.985
with the color and texture
of thigh skin,

09:30.278 --> 09:33.196
it would actually
develop as facial tissue.

09:34.615 --> 09:35.407
In other words,

09:36.033 --> 09:39.869
neutral field tissue
has the same ability

09:40.496 --> 09:42.414
to form any part
of the human body

09:42.623 --> 09:44.416
that the tissue
of a human embryo has.

09:48.254 --> 09:49.170
Let me add...

09:49.797 --> 09:51.631
that there is always
a possibility

09:51.841 --> 09:53.174
that carcinomas will form

09:53.384 --> 09:55.468
when neutral field grafts
are used internally.

09:57.263 --> 09:58.263
In this case,

09:58.973 --> 10:01.433
we're using a radical
plastic surgery technique

10:01.684 --> 10:04.894
to compensate for the lack
of heavy medical hardware.

10:05.563 --> 10:07.355
MAN: Can we treat
graft material here,

10:07.565 --> 10:08.398
Dr. Keloid?

10:08.858 --> 10:10.525
KELOID: No, Dr. Karl,

10:11.193 --> 10:12.277
the grafts will be frozen

10:12.486 --> 10:14.404
and sent
to the Sperling Institute.

10:16.490 --> 10:18.867
We'll have to keep the patient
at an operation-ready state

10:19.076 --> 10:20.243
until they come back to us.

10:20.453 --> 10:22.037
Now, I know this is going to be
trying for all of us,

10:22.246 --> 10:23.538
but it can't be helped.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.142
Her body is still in a state
of total shock.

10:44.894 --> 10:47.937
We still can't move her
to a city hospital yet.

10:48.898 --> 10:50.774
But her grafts are doing well.

10:51.984 --> 10:53.276
We've been monitoring

10:53.486 --> 10:55.654
the internal grafts
electronically,

10:56.280 --> 10:59.032
and there's a definite sign
of new tissue growth happening

10:59.241 --> 11:00.492
in the abdominal cavity.

11:01.535 --> 11:04.579
Her helmet probably saved her
from severe brain damage,

11:04.872 --> 11:06.790
but until she's
fully conscious...

11:07.333 --> 11:08.375
You won't know that either.

11:08.793 --> 11:10.293
KELOID: Well, Hart,
what can I tell ya?

11:10.503 --> 11:11.378
There is no magic.

11:12.546 --> 11:13.922
I have done my best.

11:15.800 --> 11:17.300
Now, you're welcome
to come and visit Rose

11:17.510 --> 11:18.885
any time you want.

11:20.262 --> 11:24.307
Please, believe me,
I will personally telephone you

11:24.517 --> 11:26.059
the instant Rose shows

11:26.268 --> 11:29.229
the first signs
of regaining consciousness.

12:19.321 --> 12:20.655
Jeez, when I saw them
bringing you in,

12:20.865 --> 12:22.031
I never thought I'd be
standing here talking

12:22.241 --> 12:23.074
to you a month later.

12:23.409 --> 12:24.200
How's your hand?

12:24.869 --> 12:26.703
Oh, it's okay, thanks. I think.

12:27.121 --> 12:28.288
They're gonna take
the support off

12:28.497 --> 12:30.039
later on this afternoon
at the General,

12:30.249 --> 12:31.583
so that's when I'll find out.

12:33.043 --> 12:36.087
But the pin stays in my shoulder
another month.

12:38.674 --> 12:39.966
Doesn't seem to
bother me, though,

12:40.176 --> 12:41.176
except when it gets damp.

12:43.429 --> 12:45.388
LLOYD: Yeah. Last time
I got my ears done,

12:45.598 --> 12:47.390
I could really feel it
when the weather changed.

12:48.017 --> 12:50.143
It's probably something you're
just gonna have to live with.

12:50.394 --> 12:51.895
HART: Yeah, I guess so.

12:52.938 --> 12:54.063
-Hi, Lloyd.
-<i>LLOYD: Hi.</i>

12:54.273 --> 12:55.774
-How ya doin'?
-Oh, not too bad.

12:55.983 --> 12:56.941
Putting in for phase two, huh?

12:57.151 --> 12:58.651
Yeah, a little eye tuck
this time.

12:59.236 --> 13:00.487
-Looks terrific.
-Good.

13:00.696 --> 13:01.404
Hey, let's get out of here.

13:01.614 --> 13:03.406
I've got a pack of hungry
investors waiting for me.

13:03.616 --> 13:04.657
-We'll see you.
-Okay, bye-bye.

13:12.583 --> 13:13.541
[ Groans ]

13:13.876 --> 13:16.085
I hope you've got somebody there
to help you unload that junk.

13:16.462 --> 13:18.004
I've got a bad back, you know?

13:19.465 --> 13:20.840
What are you going
to do with that?

13:21.050 --> 13:23.176
Use it as an ashtray?
[ Chuckles ]

13:50.329 --> 13:51.120
[ Flicks lighter ]

14:06.136 --> 14:07.011
[ Sighs ]

14:25.614 --> 14:27.282
[ Screaming ]

14:29.118 --> 14:31.160
[ Groaning ]

14:48.762 --> 14:50.471
[ Glass breaking ]

14:56.437 --> 14:57.896
-Rosie!
-[ Gasping ]

14:58.105 --> 15:00.064
Rosie, sweetie, take it easy.

15:00.274 --> 15:02.483
You need that juice, sweetie.
It's keeping you alive.

15:02.735 --> 15:04.444
-That's a girl.
-What are-- what are you doing?

15:04.987 --> 15:08.156
-Are we-- are we all right?
-I'm not Hart, Rosie.

15:08.699 --> 15:10.491
Hart's back in Montreal
waiting for you.

15:10.701 --> 15:12.410
I'm Lloyd.
I'm a friend of yours.

15:12.620 --> 15:13.328
Hart?

15:13.537 --> 15:15.747
Hart's back in Montreal
waiting for you.

15:16.498 --> 15:17.457
Oh.

15:18.125 --> 15:20.376
I guess--
I guess I was dreaming.

15:21.211 --> 15:22.670
I don't think you were
just dreaming.

15:22.880 --> 15:25.882
You and Hart were in a really
spectacular motorcycle crash.

15:26.383 --> 15:28.176
-Crash?
-LLOYD: Yes.

15:28.469 --> 15:30.470
You're bleeding right now.
I'd better get Dr. Keloid.

15:30.679 --> 15:32.388
Oh, no, no, no, don't go.

15:32.723 --> 15:34.057
I'm all right, really.

15:34.391 --> 15:36.100
I'm freezing cold!

15:36.977 --> 15:38.728
Ooh, you're so warm.

15:38.938 --> 15:40.521
-Hey, look, I think I'd better--
-Oh, hold me.

15:42.942 --> 15:43.816
Please.

15:44.610 --> 15:45.693
-[ Sighs ]
-Mm.

15:46.028 --> 15:47.570
I'm dying of the cold.

15:48.405 --> 15:50.615
Oh, God, that feels so...

15:51.200 --> 15:53.534
Uh, look, you don't even know
where you are, do you?

15:53.744 --> 15:54.953
Oh, God.

15:56.664 --> 15:58.539
Uh, look, this is really weird.

15:58.749 --> 16:00.458
Uh, are you sure you know
what you're...

16:00.668 --> 16:01.876
[ Groans ]

16:02.252 --> 16:04.462
Uh, I think-- I think
I cut myself or something.

16:04.922 --> 16:08.549
-[ Groans ]
-[ Moans ]

16:08.759 --> 16:09.759
Is that a knife or something
in there with you?

16:09.969 --> 16:12.011
-[ Groans ]
-[ Moans ]

16:30.614 --> 16:34.492
[ Whimpering ]

16:58.475 --> 16:59.267
[ Knock at door ]

17:00.144 --> 17:01.060
Yes?

17:02.354 --> 17:03.312
Who is it?

17:10.362 --> 17:11.279
[ Screams ]

17:11.613 --> 17:12.821
God, help me!

17:13.031 --> 17:15.491
Help me!
[ Groans ]

17:18.078 --> 17:18.828
[ Gasps ]

17:19.079 --> 17:20.704
For heaven's sake,
what happened to you?

17:21.080 --> 17:24.751
I don't know.
I can't remember anything.

17:24.960 --> 17:27.170
[ Panting ]

17:42.144 --> 17:43.686
Were you sleepwalking?

17:46.023 --> 17:48.149
Did you fall
against something outside

17:48.358 --> 17:49.484
and come in without waking up?

17:50.360 --> 17:51.194
I doubt it.

17:52.404 --> 17:54.030
It never happened to me before.

17:55.324 --> 17:56.532
Get me some stuffing.

17:57.034 --> 17:58.493
One or two sponges, as well.

17:59.787 --> 18:01.329
This wound isn't
clotting at all.

18:02.372 --> 18:03.956
I think we're going to have
to give him some coagulants

18:04.166 --> 18:05.333
to get a scab to form.

18:05.793 --> 18:07.001
Right away, Doctor.

18:16.261 --> 18:17.887
Does that hurt?

18:18.722 --> 18:20.598
I can't feel a thing.

18:21.642 --> 18:22.767
You can't?

18:23.310 --> 18:25.686
My whole right side
has no feeling in it.

18:26.396 --> 18:29.440
Just this aching
kind of tingling.

18:33.237 --> 18:34.737
-Dr. Keloid.
-Hm?

18:35.906 --> 18:37.490
Maxim would like to see you.

18:38.242 --> 18:39.450
Well, right now?

18:39.660 --> 18:41.786
He said it was important.
He's waiting in the hall.

18:42.913 --> 18:43.788
Okay.

18:45.165 --> 18:45.998
Listen.

18:48.836 --> 18:50.837
I think our friend here
may have suffered a stroke.

18:51.046 --> 18:52.463
Now, the General's
the best place for him.

18:52.673 --> 18:53.923
But before you plug him up,

18:54.133 --> 18:56.259
I want you to draw ten ccs
of blood

18:56.468 --> 18:57.927
directly from the wound
for tests.

18:58.220 --> 19:00.513
Then Steve can drive him
into the city in the ambulance.

19:00.722 --> 19:02.598
Make sure he takes along
a lot of plasma,

19:03.433 --> 19:06.686
and forget the coagulants
until the General has a chance

19:06.895 --> 19:07.937
to do an ECG on him.

19:08.522 --> 19:09.522
Will do, Doctor.

19:09.731 --> 19:10.773
Yes, Maxim, what's up?

19:10.983 --> 19:12.316
You told me to check around
the grounds

19:12.526 --> 19:14.527
to see if I could find out
how Mr. Walsh was hurt.

19:14.736 --> 19:15.862
But I could find
nothing outside,

19:16.071 --> 19:17.446
no blood, nothing.

19:17.948 --> 19:19.282
Then Nurse Rita called.

19:22.202 --> 19:22.952
[ Knocks on door ]

19:29.668 --> 19:31.169
Watch what you touch, Doctor.

19:31.378 --> 19:32.670
The police may want
to examine the room

19:32.880 --> 19:34.130
exactly the way we found it.

19:35.257 --> 19:36.883
Why the police?

19:37.634 --> 19:42.305
Well, that Mr. Walsh fellow
tried to molest her

19:42.514 --> 19:43.598
while she was still in a coma.

19:43.807 --> 19:45.516
I've seen things like that
happen before.

19:46.185 --> 19:47.393
Maybe he was drunk.

19:54.985 --> 19:57.236
The grafts are healing
amazingly well.

20:06.747 --> 20:09.749
Judy Glasberg?
You back again?

20:10.083 --> 20:12.168
Daddy didn't think the new nose
was different enough,

20:12.377 --> 20:14.003
so I'm back
for more alterations.

20:14.463 --> 20:16.839
I keep on saying to him
it looks exactly like his,

20:17.049 --> 20:17.757
and he keeps on saying,

20:17.966 --> 20:19.175
''That's why I want you
to change it.''

20:20.177 --> 20:21.219
What's this?

20:21.428 --> 20:23.763
I'm terrified to find out
what it really means.

20:39.446 --> 20:41.447
[ Heavy rainfall ]

22:57.667 --> 22:59.085
[ Cow grunting ]

22:59.294 --> 23:01.754
[ Vomits ]

23:08.220 --> 23:10.054
All right, you hold it
right there.

23:12.808 --> 23:14.600
Ah!
[ Chuckles ]

23:16.478 --> 23:18.729
Well, what have we got there?

23:20.399 --> 23:22.650
Hello, sweet honey pie.

23:24.653 --> 23:26.070
What're ya drinkin'?

23:27.280 --> 23:29.156
You come in to get out
of the cold?

23:30.450 --> 23:31.367
[ Chuckles ]

23:32.828 --> 23:34.787
I got something you
can drink off of,

23:35.372 --> 23:37.331
and it ain't no whisky neither.

23:37.624 --> 23:39.166
[ Chuckles ]

23:39.543 --> 23:41.001
Honey pie.

23:41.294 --> 23:42.503
[ Chuckles ]

23:45.674 --> 23:48.092
Oh, you've got blood
on your mouth.

23:48.927 --> 23:51.595
Yeah. You like me, huh?

23:51.805 --> 23:54.974
-[ Gasps ]
-I can tell you do. Huh?

23:55.267 --> 23:57.059
[ Chuckles ]

24:02.441 --> 24:05.693
[ Screaming ]

24:07.320 --> 24:09.405
[ Screaming ]

24:12.325 --> 24:13.451
<i>Little flower</i>

24:13.743 --> 24:15.202
<i>Benihana</i>

24:16.121 --> 24:17.663
<i>What a turn on</i>

24:18.540 --> 24:20.708
<i>When you call my name</i>

24:20.959 --> 24:22.501
<i>When we make love</i>

24:23.086 --> 24:24.879
<i>In the darkness</i>

24:25.422 --> 24:27.465
<i>Every night</i>

24:30.010 --> 24:32.052
<i>And you whisper</i>

24:32.429 --> 24:34.305
<i>That I feel like</i>

24:34.973 --> 24:36.432
<i>A flower</i>

24:36.933 --> 24:39.310
<i>'Cause I'm, oh, so smooth</i>

24:39.519 --> 24:41.520
[ Heavy rainfall ]

24:50.238 --> 24:52.198
<i>Having you fills my life</i>

24:54.159 --> 24:57.077
<i>Night time passes on by</i>

24:58.914 --> 25:01.540
<i>Every time that we're close</i>

25:01.750 --> 25:04.084
<i>Our loving gets better</i>

25:04.294 --> 25:05.252
<i>Better and better</i>

25:05.462 --> 25:06.212
<i>Yeah</i>

25:06.421 --> 25:08.964
<i>-Better, better</i>
<i>-Better and better</i>

25:10.842 --> 25:12.885
[ Phone ringing ]

25:16.932 --> 25:20.017
-[ Gasps ]
-[ Ringing tone ]

25:20.268 --> 25:21.560
Come on.

25:21.978 --> 25:23.854
[ Shivering ]

25:28.360 --> 25:30.528
[ Gasps ]
Hurry.

25:34.699 --> 25:36.033
<i>Oh, honey</i>

25:36.576 --> 25:37.910
<i>It feels so good</i>

25:38.119 --> 25:39.078
<i>Benihana</i>

25:56.555 --> 25:58.806
Hey, Lloyd, where you going?
You can't leave yet.

25:59.182 --> 26:00.099
I mean, they don't even know

26:00.308 --> 26:02.184
why you're bleeding
all over the place.

26:02.727 --> 26:04.270
Ah, it's slowed down
to a trickle.

26:04.854 --> 26:05.813
No problem.

26:06.064 --> 26:08.274
No problem, huh?
How's the arm?

26:09.192 --> 26:09.984
It's fine.

26:11.111 --> 26:11.902
MAN: All right.

26:13.196 --> 26:14.071
If the night nurse comes around,

26:14.281 --> 26:15.906
I'll-- I'll tell her
you're in the can, eh?

26:16.116 --> 26:16.865
How's that?

26:17.075 --> 26:18.033
Terrific.

26:18.994 --> 26:19.785
Take care of yourself.

26:21.037 --> 26:22.621
Yeah. You too.

26:52.193 --> 26:53.485
Take me to Camelford.

26:53.945 --> 26:55.446
I'll tell you
where to go from there.

27:18.928 --> 27:19.928
Oh!

27:20.597 --> 27:21.347
[ Sighs ]

27:21.556 --> 27:23.140
I thought everyone was asleep.

27:25.018 --> 27:26.518
Do you mind
if I get in with you?

27:27.771 --> 27:29.563
I've been lying in bed
for so long.

27:30.565 --> 27:32.066
My body aches all over.

27:38.740 --> 27:40.532
I'm so glad I ran into you.

27:41.368 --> 27:43.702
Uh, well, I think I'd better be
getting out, now.

27:44.329 --> 27:45.913
[ Sighs ]
I'm getting all wrinkly.

27:46.122 --> 27:48.999
Oh, no. Not yet. You haven't
even told me your name.

27:51.670 --> 27:52.836
Judy Glasberg.

27:53.171 --> 27:55.381
[ Screaming ]

28:02.847 --> 28:06.016
[ Screaming and gasping ]

28:06.810 --> 28:08.310
[ Gurgling ]

28:08.520 --> 28:11.689
[ Screaming and gasping ]

28:17.487 --> 28:20.197
[ Softly moaning ]

28:34.212 --> 28:36.046
So I says to the guy
he shouldn't let his wife

28:36.256 --> 28:37.423
push him around like that.

28:38.216 --> 28:39.299
Mister, you okay?

28:40.176 --> 28:41.427
You look a bit sick.

28:42.262 --> 28:44.138
Want me to pull over
to the side of the road?

28:45.932 --> 28:48.142
-[ Snarling ]
-[ Screams ]

28:48.727 --> 28:51.895
[ Tires screeching ]

28:52.897 --> 28:55.441
-[ Snarling ]
-[ Screams ]

29:22.093 --> 29:24.136
[ Phone ringing ]

29:28.975 --> 29:30.768
<i>-Hello?</i>
<i>-ROSE: Oh, Hart.</i>

29:30.977 --> 29:33.937
Listen, I'm in terrible trouble.

29:34.272 --> 29:35.564
You gotta help me.

29:36.191 --> 29:38.317
<i>HART:</i>
<i>Rose. Is that really you?</i>

29:38.860 --> 29:41.069
<i>Where are ya?</i>
<i>Are you all right?</i>

29:41.279 --> 29:43.197
Hart--
Hart, can you hear me?

29:43.406 --> 29:44.782
<i>HART: Yes, I can hear you.</i>

29:45.325 --> 29:49.369
Listen, you gotta come quick,
you gotta come quick and get me.

29:49.579 --> 29:51.163
-RITA: Rose.
<i>-HART: Rose?</i>

29:51.498 --> 29:52.664
Tell me what's wrong.

29:52.957 --> 29:55.459
-You all right, dear?
<i>-HART: Rose, what's wrong?</i>

29:56.085 --> 29:57.169
Come on.

29:57.378 --> 29:58.212
[ Click ]

30:05.428 --> 30:08.013
What the hell was the number
of that place, anyhow?

30:14.395 --> 30:15.270
[ Knock at door ]

30:16.898 --> 30:19.274
Doctor, I think you better
come with me.

30:28.576 --> 30:30.702
I think, uh...

30:30.954 --> 30:33.163
I'd like to talk to her
alone first.

30:33.915 --> 30:34.706
Okay.

31:02.902 --> 31:05.737
-Rose, I'm Dr. Keloid.
-[ Sniffling ]

31:06.739 --> 31:08.031
Dan Keloid.

31:10.493 --> 31:12.035
I'm here to help you,
sweetheart.

31:12.328 --> 31:14.454
Oh, Doctor!
[ Sobs ]

31:16.165 --> 31:19.167
There, there. It's all right.

31:19.377 --> 31:20.377
[ Sniffling ]

31:24.424 --> 31:26.842
Rose, I promise you
we won't talk about anything

31:27.051 --> 31:29.887
except how you're feeling, okay?

31:30.388 --> 31:31.179
Good.

31:31.890 --> 31:33.932
First thing I want to do is
check out the skin grafts

31:34.142 --> 31:34.808
we did for you.

31:35.018 --> 31:36.852
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, no.

31:37.270 --> 31:39.187
Well, what's the matter, Rose?
Are you in pain?

31:40.440 --> 31:41.690
Talk to me.

31:42.066 --> 31:43.525
It's the only way I have
of understanding

31:43.735 --> 31:44.484
what's bothering you.

31:44.694 --> 31:46.278
I'm hideous, Doctor.

31:47.030 --> 31:50.782
I'm crazy, and I'm a monster.
[ Sobs ]

31:50.992 --> 31:52.159
Now, come on, Rose.

31:52.368 --> 31:54.202
There's just about nothing
we can't fix

31:54.412 --> 31:56.163
if we know what's wrong.

31:57.248 --> 32:02.169
Now, don't play any more games
and do as I tell you.

32:03.630 --> 32:07.674
That's enough, huh?
Okay, there.

32:08.134 --> 32:09.718
There.
[ Yawns ]

32:09.928 --> 32:12.846
Oh! Look at Potato Man.

32:13.473 --> 32:15.807
See how Potato Man
loves Ketchup Man?

32:19.228 --> 32:21.229
[ Telephone rings ]

32:22.357 --> 32:24.441
-Do you believe that?
-[ Ringing continues ]

32:25.068 --> 32:26.234
Excuse me.

32:28.738 --> 32:29.571
[ Sighs ]

32:30.531 --> 32:31.949
Hello, who's this?
What do you want?

32:32.158 --> 32:33.241
Do you know what time it is?

32:33.910 --> 32:34.743
Listen, Murray,

32:34.953 --> 32:37.204
I hate like hell to bother you
at a time like this,

32:37.413 --> 32:39.873
but I'm going out of my skull.

32:40.625 --> 32:41.375
Well, that's all right,

32:41.584 --> 32:43.627
I-- I was up
with the baby anyhow.

32:43.836 --> 32:44.711
What's-- what's the matter?

32:45.171 --> 32:47.089
I just got a phone call
from the clinic.

32:47.298 --> 32:48.006
<i>MURRAY: Yeah?</i>

32:48.216 --> 32:50.217
-From Rose.
<i>-MURRAY: Who?</i>

32:50.969 --> 32:52.302
From Rose!

32:53.304 --> 32:55.806
She's supposed to be in a coma,
for God's sake.

32:56.140 --> 32:59.434
<i>She said she was in trouble.</i>
<i>She wants me to help her.</i>

32:59.644 --> 33:01.979
<i>She wants me to come up there</i>
<i>right now and get her!</i>

33:02.271 --> 33:05.941
Look, Hart, she's probably
just frightened and confused.

33:06.150 --> 33:08.485
Did you call-- did you call
Danny back at the clinic?

33:09.153 --> 33:10.946
I got a tape recorder.

33:11.155 --> 33:11.947
[ Sighs ]

33:12.573 --> 33:13.991
I left a message.

33:14.867 --> 33:16.410
[ Sighs ]
Okay.

33:17.745 --> 33:19.746
Okay, I'll tell you
what I'll do. I'll, uh...

33:20.915 --> 33:22.916
I'll call Danny on his
private line right now,

33:23.126 --> 33:25.293
and I'll tell him that Rosie's
up making phone calls

33:25.503 --> 33:26.586
in the middle of the night,
okay?

33:26.796 --> 33:28.547
Look, I'll pick you up
in about an hour,

33:28.965 --> 33:30.382
and I'll drive you
over to the clinic.

33:30.591 --> 33:33.051
<i>-MURRAY: How's that grab you?</i>
-Okay, Murray.

33:34.429 --> 33:36.430
-Thanks a hell of a lot.
<i>-MURRAY: Yeah.</i>

33:36.723 --> 33:38.557
<i>MURRAY:</i>
<i>You bet. See you soon.</i>

33:38.933 --> 33:39.725
[ Click ]

34:12.091 --> 34:13.050
Does that hurt?

34:13.301 --> 34:16.136
[ Sniffles ]
No, it doesn't hurt.

34:34.447 --> 34:36.156
How long have you
been conscious, Rose?

34:36.699 --> 34:37.908
Do you know?

34:39.534 --> 34:40.827
A couple of days.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.413
KELOID: Do you feel weak?

34:44.706 --> 34:45.748
I feel strong.

34:46.626 --> 34:48.210
I feel very strong.

34:49.337 --> 34:51.129
KELOID: Rita tells me you
wouldn't let her attach you

34:51.339 --> 34:52.839
to your intravenous
nutrient bottles.

34:53.049 --> 34:53.757
Why?

34:54.092 --> 34:55.717
I don't need them.

34:55.967 --> 34:57.385
They make me feel sick.

34:57.595 --> 34:59.137
KELOID: I don't understand.

35:00.348 --> 35:02.808
They've got to be
your only source of food.

35:03.101 --> 35:04.142
They're not.

35:04.936 --> 35:06.895
They haven't been
for a couple of days.

35:09.232 --> 35:11.358
-Not since that man.
-KELOID: Man?

35:12.443 --> 35:14.027
What are you talking about?

35:14.529 --> 35:15.403
ROSE: I'll show you.

35:17.281 --> 35:19.157
[ Screams ]

35:28.000 --> 35:30.043
[ Whimpers ]

36:26.058 --> 36:28.935
-Half a barbecue chicken to go.
-Yes, sir.

36:31.022 --> 36:32.814
Half a barbecue chicken to go.

36:34.650 --> 36:36.902
And, uh, will that be all?

36:38.112 --> 36:40.322
Oh. Mister?

36:41.032 --> 36:42.616
Did you know you're bleeding?

36:43.618 --> 36:45.160
Ah, it's nothing.

36:45.995 --> 36:47.662
Must've had a
rough night, buddy.

36:47.997 --> 36:49.456
Ah, I can't remember too good.

36:49.749 --> 36:50.832
Here's your order, Sam.

36:53.753 --> 36:55.545
I think that one's mine, buddy.

36:56.631 --> 36:58.423
I said I think that one's mine.

36:59.175 --> 37:01.509
I've gotta eat!
I've gotta eat!

37:01.719 --> 37:03.762
Look, I don't hit
nobody with glasses.

37:03.971 --> 37:05.764
[ Snarling ]

37:09.060 --> 37:10.852
Now, calm down.

37:12.104 --> 37:13.271
-[ Snarls ]
-Hey!

37:13.481 --> 37:14.814
[ Screams ]

37:18.861 --> 37:20.779
You're sure you want
to do this one, Dan?

37:21.239 --> 37:23.156
Louise and I could handle it,
no trouble.

37:24.450 --> 37:26.534
I'll-- I'll be fine.

37:27.453 --> 37:29.204
You were pretty groggy
this morning.

37:30.456 --> 37:31.706
Cut yourself shaving?

37:32.875 --> 37:34.709
No, I'll be fine.
I'll be fine.

37:44.220 --> 37:44.970
KELOID: Scalpel.

37:58.526 --> 37:59.484
Sponge.

38:10.705 --> 38:12.372
<i>...inside an empty bourbon</i>

38:12.581 --> 38:13.915
<i>We're going down</i>

38:14.125 --> 38:15.667
<i>You're down in the town</i>

38:16.210 --> 38:19.212
<i>To have a good time</i>
<i>and drink your sweet wine</i>

38:19.547 --> 38:22.674
<i>Here I come</i>
<i>with a bellyful of rocks</i>

38:23.009 --> 38:25.677
<i>Put you right up inside</i>
<i>an empty bourbon</i>

38:25.886 --> 38:28.722
<i>Wanna keep that thing</i>
<i>all the way...</i>

38:45.906 --> 38:48.533
Do you want me to complete
the stitching, Dr. Keloid?

38:49.660 --> 38:51.953
I need something to cut with,
Dr. Rushton.

38:52.538 --> 38:54.331
You want the scissors now,
Doctor?

38:54.874 --> 38:57.542
Yes. Scissors, now.

38:59.879 --> 39:01.087
Scissors.

39:02.131 --> 39:03.673
-[ Grunts ]
-Dan!

39:04.508 --> 39:07.260
-[ Screams ]
-[ Snarling ]

39:08.262 --> 39:09.929
KARL: Stop it!

39:10.181 --> 39:12.057
-Oh!
-[ Screaming ]

39:15.394 --> 39:17.395
KARL: Are you crazy
or something? Stop it!

39:17.605 --> 39:19.773
-[ Snarling ]
-[ Screaming ]

39:23.027 --> 39:24.694
-[ Screaming ]
-[ Metal crashing ]

39:25.946 --> 39:28.782
Rita! Rita, he's gone crazy,
he's gone crazy!

39:28.991 --> 39:29.949
-He's killing everyone.
-What?

39:30.159 --> 39:31.284
Come with me!
We've gotta do something!

39:31.494 --> 39:32.202
Wait! Calm down.

39:32.411 --> 39:34.829
-Come with me!
-Who? Louise?

39:36.248 --> 39:37.791
<i>MAN ON TV: Would you like</i>
<i>to have him be a policeman</i>

39:38.000 --> 39:38.875
<i>and arrest you?</i>

39:39.293 --> 39:41.086
<i>Have him be a doctor</i>
<i>and examine you?</i>

39:41.712 --> 39:44.339
<i>Or have him be a lawyer</i>
<i>and defend you?</i>

39:44.965 --> 39:46.674
<i>Those are your choices.</i>
<i>Claire?</i>

39:52.890 --> 39:54.891
[ Gasping ]

40:04.193 --> 40:06.069
[ Sighs ]
Oh.

40:08.948 --> 40:11.324
<i>MAN ON RADIO: The man,</i>
<i>now identified as 43-year-old</i>

40:11.534 --> 40:12.909
<i>Fred Atkins of Camelford,</i>

40:13.119 --> 40:14.869
<i>went berserk this morning</i>
<i>during an argument</i>

40:15.079 --> 40:16.496
<i>over who was to be served first</i>

40:16.705 --> 40:18.706
<i>and bit the counter girl</i>
<i>on the arm.</i>

40:18.958 --> 40:21.709
<i>The man was subdued</i>
<i>by an unidentified truck driver</i>

40:21.919 --> 40:23.294
<i>and the truck stop</i>
<i>diner's cook,</i>

40:23.504 --> 40:26.381
<i>but died of unknown causes</i>
<i>before police arrived.</i>

40:26.882 --> 40:28.299
<i>Local health</i>
<i>authorities suspect</i>

40:28.509 --> 40:29.843
<i>that rabies might be involved</i>

40:30.052 --> 40:31.928
<i>and have vaccinated</i>
<i>everyone concerned.</i>

40:32.638 --> 40:35.723
<i>Now, after this brief pause</i>
<i>for station identification--</i>

40:35.933 --> 40:37.350
This must be the place
they were talking about

40:37.560 --> 40:38.435
on the radio.

40:38.894 --> 40:40.562
Huh? Wanna go in for a bite?

40:41.063 --> 40:41.896
[ Chuckles ]

40:42.231 --> 40:43.314
No, no thanks.

41:16.432 --> 41:18.391
-What's going on over there?
-Where?

41:21.270 --> 41:23.146
The place is crawling
with police.

41:24.231 --> 41:25.398
Hey, you're right.

41:26.025 --> 41:28.234
-Oh, Christ, no.
-What's the matter?

41:28.486 --> 41:31.529
It's Rose. It's gotta be.
Something's happened to Rose.

41:31.739 --> 41:32.655
Oh, Hart, take it easy.

41:32.865 --> 41:34.365
They wouldn't have
all these cars just for that.

41:34.575 --> 41:35.742
It must be something else.

41:36.744 --> 41:38.495
Okay, Murray,
come on, come on.

41:41.874 --> 41:43.124
Take it easy, will ya, Hart?

41:45.085 --> 41:47.670
[ Door ajar alarm buzzing ]

41:49.006 --> 41:49.797
[ Car door closing ]

41:56.764 --> 41:58.848
Bill! Bill, what's going on
around here?

41:59.058 --> 42:00.934
-And where's Dr. Keloid?
-Murray, thank God you're here.

42:01.685 --> 42:02.685
It's been a nightmare.

42:03.270 --> 42:04.938
I'm trying to
find my girlfriend.

42:05.731 --> 42:07.232
Uh, she's a patient here.

42:07.900 --> 42:08.942
She was here last night,

42:09.151 --> 42:11.319
but now nobody seems to know
where she is.

42:12.238 --> 42:13.488
We've got a young girl
downstairs.

42:13.864 --> 42:14.989
You wanna take a look at her?

42:15.824 --> 42:17.116
Is her name Rose?

42:18.035 --> 42:19.202
We don't know.
We didn't ask her.

42:19.662 --> 42:20.578
Come on.

42:20.788 --> 42:22.705
Uh, tell the chief I'm
downstairs gettin' an ID.

42:23.123 --> 42:24.123
Be back in a flash.

42:25.501 --> 42:26.584
[ Siren wails outside ]

42:27.211 --> 42:29.546
So you are Dr. Keloid's
business partner?

42:29.755 --> 42:30.922
Yeah, that's right, I am. Now--

42:31.131 --> 42:32.924
Come with me, please.
Excuse me.

42:34.843 --> 42:37.262
-Bill?
-No, you go, Murray.

42:37.471 --> 42:39.931
I-- I can't. I've seen it.

42:41.767 --> 42:43.685
OFFICER: Mr. Cypher, please.

42:49.108 --> 42:53.027
Couple of my men got bitten.
Those rabies shots are killers.

42:53.362 --> 42:56.489
Think I'd rather take my chances
on getting sick instead.

42:59.868 --> 43:00.702
How is he, doc?

43:16.010 --> 43:19.304
Say, you say-- you say he
got bitten. Bitten by what?

43:20.097 --> 43:22.432
-By that.
-What?

43:22.850 --> 43:24.058
Go ahead, take a look.

43:29.565 --> 43:33.818
-Oh, God!
-[ Snarling ]

43:37.156 --> 43:39.449
OFFICER: Can you confirm
the identification of this man

43:39.658 --> 43:41.409
as Dr. Daniel Keloid?

43:41.660 --> 43:43.453
[ Snarling continues ]

43:57.885 --> 44:00.053
Come here. Can't see anything
from there.

44:04.767 --> 44:06.267
HART: Oh.

44:07.436 --> 44:10.271
-[ Sighs ]
-Is that Rose?

44:11.690 --> 44:14.901
No, no, it's not Rose.

44:20.240 --> 44:22.533
Hey, Rose, want a bite?

44:23.243 --> 44:24.410
Steak on a bun.

44:24.870 --> 44:25.620
It's real good.

44:25.829 --> 44:27.705
Mm. I wouldn't mind
just one bite.

44:28.374 --> 44:29.290
You sure?

44:42.805 --> 44:44.806
Mmm, it's fabulous.

45:13.627 --> 45:14.502
That's okay.

45:15.003 --> 45:15.753
It's the last time

45:15.963 --> 45:16.963
I'm going to eat
at that greasy spoon,

45:17.172 --> 45:17.839
I'll tell you that.

45:18.048 --> 45:19.716
That's it, come on.
Get it all out.

45:19.925 --> 45:21.884
-[ Retching ]
-Okay?

45:22.261 --> 45:23.052
All right.

45:23.262 --> 45:24.721
Just put your arm around me,
and I'll lift you up

45:24.930 --> 45:25.805
back into the cabin.

45:26.098 --> 45:28.933
We'll get some soup or something
at the next stop, all right?

45:32.938 --> 45:33.771
Watch out.

46:19.610 --> 46:20.610
Is something wrong?

46:22.488 --> 46:23.321
Hey, buddy.

46:24.490 --> 46:25.281
What?

46:28.494 --> 46:29.744
Oh, I, uh...

46:30.788 --> 46:33.039
Oh, jeez, I must have dozed off.

46:33.248 --> 46:35.583
I, uh... I was driving.

46:36.543 --> 46:37.293
Jeez.

46:37.503 --> 46:38.211
Well, it's good.

46:38.420 --> 46:40.379
We find too many
of you guys taking pills

46:40.589 --> 46:42.256
to keep yourselves
going all day and all night.

46:44.593 --> 46:46.344
-Thanks.
-Next time, though, uh...

46:46.553 --> 46:48.221
try and pick a better spot
to pull over,

46:48.430 --> 46:49.514
This road's kind of narrow.

46:51.058 --> 46:53.392
Yeah, thanks. I will.
Sorry.

46:54.228 --> 46:55.895
Yeah, okay.
Have a nice day.

47:21.547 --> 47:23.339
-Hi.
-Hi. Where are you going?

47:23.549 --> 47:25.550
-Montreal. Where are you going?
-Same place.

47:25.759 --> 47:26.551
Great.

47:27.386 --> 47:28.177
Whoo!

47:28.595 --> 47:29.387
Oh!

47:29.596 --> 47:31.305
You know, I was beginning
to think I'd never

47:31.515 --> 47:32.265
get home again.

47:46.071 --> 47:48.573
[ Police radio chatter ]

47:52.035 --> 47:54.245
Claude Lapointe,
Quebec Bureau of Health,

47:54.663 --> 47:55.705
official business.

47:55.998 --> 47:58.040
-What's up?
-Sorry, officer.

47:58.250 --> 48:00.126
You can't go in
unless you're willing to stay.

48:00.419 --> 48:02.378
The whole station's
under quarantine.

48:03.005 --> 48:04.797
We think we've got an epidemic.

48:06.425 --> 48:07.174
Hello, Mindy?

48:07.384 --> 48:08.384
I want you to blow
in this thing.

48:08.594 --> 48:10.011
-Yeah. How are you?
-The two of you.

48:10.679 --> 48:12.013
-The light's gonna be red here.
-Good.

48:12.556 --> 48:13.598
Listen, uh...

48:14.141 --> 48:16.434
I thought that Rose might try
and get in touch with ya.

48:18.020 --> 48:19.729
Yeah. She what?
She called you?

48:21.189 --> 48:22.523
-Okay, blow.
-She's on her way over?

48:22.733 --> 48:24.942
-No, I feel fine. Honest.
-That's incredible.

48:25.152 --> 48:26.402
You gotta blow in this thing.
Will ya?

48:26.612 --> 48:27.320
Ah! That's silly.

48:27.529 --> 48:28.988
Oh, you wouldn't believe
what's happening here.

48:29.197 --> 48:29.864
Just blow.

48:30.073 --> 48:31.240
-Come on!
-It's crazy time.

48:31.783 --> 48:33.659
-Yeah.
-Listen, you gotta blow in it.

48:34.661 --> 48:35.703
You ain't walking out of here
till you blow in this thing.

48:35.913 --> 48:36.621
Well, listen.

48:36.830 --> 48:37.955
-When she gets there...
-All right.

48:38.165 --> 48:38.956
Blow!

48:39.166 --> 48:39.916
...tell her I'm going
to be stuck

48:40.125 --> 48:41.334
in a Camelford cop shop

48:41.543 --> 48:42.710
for at least 48 hours.

48:43.545 --> 48:46.589
But look, when she gets there,
you keep her there for me, okay?

48:47.758 --> 48:48.549
Okay.

48:49.509 --> 48:51.344
Okay, Mindy. Ciao.

49:02.481 --> 49:04.815
That's his truck, all right.

49:13.075 --> 49:14.283
Hey, you seen Smooth Eddy?

49:14.493 --> 49:15.242
He's got the lead truck,

49:15.452 --> 49:17.078
and I can't find
the son of a bitch.

49:17.496 --> 49:19.664
Think I seen him in back before.
He didn't look too good.

49:19.873 --> 49:20.915
Whaddya mean,
he didn't look too good?

49:21.124 --> 49:22.583
Smooth Eddy always looks good.

49:23.043 --> 49:24.669
He looks sick.
You know, nauseous.

49:24.878 --> 49:26.337
Aw, what the fuck
are we runnin' here,

49:26.546 --> 49:27.672
a nursery?

49:45.440 --> 49:48.526
Eddy. Hey, Eddy,
are you in there?

49:51.530 --> 49:54.073
Goddamn truck drivers.
You can't trust 'em.

49:54.282 --> 49:55.783
-You al--
-[ Snarling ]

49:58.036 --> 49:58.828
Hey!

50:00.205 --> 50:00.955
Hey!

50:01.164 --> 50:02.540
[ Screams ]

50:07.004 --> 50:07.795
[ Groans ]

50:16.805 --> 50:18.472
<i>MAN ON TV: The health officials</i>
<i>have said they consider</i>

50:18.682 --> 50:20.558
<i>the outbreak of the new strain</i>
<i>of rabies</i>

50:20.767 --> 50:23.144
<i>as being potentially</i>
<i>the worst of this century.</i>

50:24.104 --> 50:25.646
<i>At the police station</i>
<i>in Camelford,</i>

50:25.856 --> 50:26.689
<i>Kathy Draper talked to</i>

50:26.940 --> 50:28.315
<i>Quebec Bureau of Health</i>
<i>official</i>

50:28.525 --> 50:29.483
<i>Claude Lapointe.</i>

50:31.445 --> 50:33.779
<i>This is not just a question</i>
<i>of swine flu</i>

50:33.989 --> 50:35.031
<i>or something like that.</i>

50:35.407 --> 50:37.950
<i>We have already several deaths</i>
<i>on our hands</i>

50:38.160 --> 50:39.952
<i>in this one small area alone,</i>

50:40.162 --> 50:41.704
<i>and the main problem is...</i>

50:41.913 --> 50:43.831
<i>we don't know</i>
<i>what we're up against.</i>

50:44.082 --> 50:46.542
<i>Are you saying this is not</i>
<i>an outbreak of rabies?</i>

50:46.752 --> 50:48.919
<i>I'm not saying that.</i>
<i>I'm not saying that, exactly.</i>

50:49.171 --> 50:51.047
<i>But it must be</i>
<i>a new strain of rabies,</i>

50:51.256 --> 50:53.924
<i>because there are</i>
<i>symptoms involved which we,</i>

50:54.134 --> 50:55.384
<i>and even the world</i>
<i>health community,</i>

50:55.594 --> 50:56.719
<i>do not seem to be</i>
<i>familiar with.</i>

50:57.304 --> 50:58.679
<i>What are these symptoms?</i>

50:59.306 --> 51:03.392
<i>Well, the period of incubation</i>
<i>of this disease is very brief,</i>

51:03.602 --> 51:05.394
<i>maybe six, eight hours</i>
<i>at the most.</i>

51:05.604 --> 51:08.439
<i>Now, that's quick, much quicker</i>
<i>than normal rabies.</i>

51:08.857 --> 51:12.610
<i>Then, the-- the victim, uh...</i>
<i>begins to sweat,</i>

51:12.819 --> 51:14.904
<i>to shake, to foam at the mouth.</i>

51:15.197 --> 51:16.197
<i>That's not so rare.</i>

51:16.406 --> 51:19.658
<i>What is rare is that</i>
<i>the victim always,</i>

51:19.993 --> 51:21.077
<i>with this new disease,</i>

51:21.286 --> 51:24.747
<i>uh, becomes violent</i>
<i>and wants to bite somebody new.</i>

51:25.332 --> 51:28.834
<i>Uh... and this crazy phase</i>
<i>is followed by a coma</i>

51:29.044 --> 51:31.045
<i>and then, in every case</i>
<i>we know, by death.</i>

51:31.254 --> 51:33.130
<i>It's strange,</i>
<i>very, very strange.</i>

51:33.381 --> 51:35.633
<i>What advice do you have</i>
<i>for our viewers?</i>

51:36.384 --> 51:39.053
<i>The disease spreads through</i>
<i>the saliva of the victim.</i>

51:39.262 --> 51:41.305
<i>The saliva is very contagious.</i>

51:41.681 --> 51:44.141
<i>It dribbles into open wounds</i>
<i>and cuts and--</i>

51:44.434 --> 51:46.519
<i>and causes immediate infection.</i>

51:47.312 --> 51:51.357
<i>-So?</i>
<i>-So don't let anybody bite you.</i>

51:51.566 --> 51:53.609
<i>And if somebody does,</i>
<i>find a doctor</i>

51:53.819 --> 51:55.277
<i>who can give you rabies shots</i>
<i>immediately.</i>

51:55.487 --> 51:56.362
[ Knock at door ]

51:56.571 --> 51:58.656
<i>DRAPER: I heard you mention</i>
<i>the Black Plague of London</i>

51:58.865 --> 52:00.157
<i>just before we went on the air.</i>

52:00.367 --> 52:01.367
<i>Is that what you mean?</i>

52:01.576 --> 52:03.619
<i>LAPOINTE: We sometimes</i>
<i>like to be dramatic</i>

52:03.829 --> 52:04.703
<i>about these things.</i>

52:05.038 --> 52:07.248
Surprise.
I'm amongst the living.

52:07.457 --> 52:09.416
Oh! Come in!

52:09.626 --> 52:10.209
Oh.

52:10.418 --> 52:12.169
<i>LAPOINTE: And we</i>
<i>get excited...</i>

52:14.047 --> 52:16.298
You got anything in there
I might wanna read?

52:20.846 --> 52:22.012
[ Sighs ]

52:22.931 --> 52:24.974
I'm starting to go stir crazy
already.

52:25.475 --> 52:27.184
Yeah, this is actually
pretty exciting stuff

52:27.394 --> 52:28.435
once you know
how to interpret it.

52:29.521 --> 52:30.479
Really.

52:33.066 --> 52:36.569
Whew. Ugh. I can't see straight
any more.

52:36.778 --> 52:39.446
I think I'm going
on automatic pilot.

52:41.324 --> 52:43.159
Oh, boy.

52:44.828 --> 52:46.787
I just can't believe
they're all dead.

52:46.955 --> 52:48.205
[ Glass breaking ]

52:48.415 --> 52:50.332
George, for God's sakes!

52:50.542 --> 52:52.168
Can't you understand
what I'm saying?

52:52.836 --> 52:53.627
Stand back!

52:54.713 --> 52:55.963
Sit on the floor
and put your hands

52:56.173 --> 52:56.922
on your head.

52:57.465 --> 52:58.799
Get in the cell.
Do what I tell ya.

52:59.342 --> 53:00.968
[ Groaning ]

53:01.219 --> 53:02.887
Give me room, I'm coming in.
Quick!

53:03.388 --> 53:05.806
[ Growling ]

53:09.060 --> 53:10.728
[ Gunshots ]

53:22.574 --> 53:24.575
They gave him rabies shots.

53:25.202 --> 53:27.161
He got bitten up
at that facelift place,

53:27.370 --> 53:29.413
and he was the first one
to get the shots.

53:30.123 --> 53:32.541
They didn't do him any
damn good, did they?

53:40.675 --> 53:42.343
Where are you going?

53:42.677 --> 53:44.595
Oh, I think I have to go out
for a while.

53:45.055 --> 53:47.181
Oh, Rosie, I feel so stupid.

53:48.892 --> 53:50.851
I haven't been much
of a hostess.

53:51.645 --> 53:53.520
Why-- why don't you
stay here?

53:53.730 --> 53:54.772
There must be something
in the fridge

53:54.981 --> 53:55.731
I can tempt you with.

53:55.941 --> 53:57.858
No, Mindy, thanks,
but it's not that.

53:58.485 --> 54:00.444
I just have to get out
into the fresh air again.

54:00.654 --> 54:02.738
It's a real experience for me
just to walk down the street.

54:02.948 --> 54:04.281
Oh, well, then, let me
come with you.

54:04.491 --> 54:05.241
No, no, no.

54:05.450 --> 54:06.700
You stay here
and finish your laundry,

54:06.910 --> 54:08.577
and I won't be gone too long.

54:09.412 --> 54:10.329
Okay, Rosie.

54:11.164 --> 54:13.082
Uh, well, if you get dizzy
or anything, call me.

54:13.416 --> 54:16.293
Okay, I will, don't worry.

54:16.503 --> 54:17.836
Yeah, bye.

55:00.088 --> 55:01.630
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>It was beautiful.</i>

55:02.132 --> 55:03.173
<i>MAN IN FILM: Yes.</i>

55:04.426 --> 55:05.592
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>My first experience</i>

55:05.802 --> 55:08.387
<i>was... like a bad trip.</i>

55:09.973 --> 55:11.849
<i>It was such a let-down.</i>

55:12.434 --> 55:14.310
<i>MAN IN FILM: That happens</i>
<i>to a lot of young girls.</i>

55:15.770 --> 55:17.146
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>I take love seriously,</i>

55:17.355 --> 55:18.147
<i>you know.</i>

55:20.191 --> 55:21.400
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>So I see.</i>

55:23.820 --> 55:25.446
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>Thanks to you, I'm free.</i>

55:27.032 --> 55:29.199
<i>My dream's reality.</i>

55:31.119 --> 55:33.203
<i>And reality's like a dream.</i>

55:34.497 --> 55:36.582
<i>You're so good</i>
<i>to be with usually.</i>

55:37.751 --> 55:39.793
<i>I wish it could last forever.</i>

55:48.595 --> 55:50.721
<i>-MAN IN FILM: Wake up!</i>
-[ Woman yawns ]

55:53.183 --> 55:54.808
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: I must be</i>
<i>dreaming again.</i>

55:55.852 --> 55:57.311
<i>I don't want to wake up.</i>

55:57.645 --> 55:58.854
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>But you're not dreaming.</i>

55:59.064 --> 55:59.980
<i>Look at that.</i>

56:00.648 --> 56:01.690
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: Mmm.</i>

56:05.487 --> 56:07.154
Excuse me.
I didn't mean to touch you.

56:07.947 --> 56:08.739
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: No.</i>

56:09.783 --> 56:10.991
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>Have you anyone to call?</i>

56:12.494 --> 56:14.620
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: I think I have.</i>
<i>Why? You want me to leave?</i>

56:14.829 --> 56:17.998
<i>-MAN IN FILM: No.</i>
-Well, pardon me for existing.

56:19.209 --> 56:21.251
I thought you did it on purpose.

56:21.461 --> 56:22.961
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: Why not?</i>

56:23.171 --> 56:23.962
No, really.

56:24.714 --> 56:27.174
I was just taking my coat off,
and it brushed against you.

56:29.010 --> 56:29.802
I'm sorry.

56:30.553 --> 56:32.096
I really like
seeing these movies,

56:32.305 --> 56:34.014
but men always bother me.

56:34.682 --> 56:36.392
Guess I'm a little paranoid.

56:37.644 --> 56:38.435
Well, look,

56:39.354 --> 56:41.688
if I was to come over there
and sit next to you,

56:42.690 --> 56:44.233
everybody will think
we're together,

56:45.276 --> 56:46.735
and you can watch it in peace.

56:48.738 --> 56:51.448
All I ask is a couple
of handfuls of popcorn.

56:51.699 --> 56:52.616
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>I'm glad my father's</i>

56:52.826 --> 56:53.992
<i>got an apartment</i>
<i>in this building.</i>

56:54.202 --> 56:55.285
Okay. Come on.

56:55.703 --> 56:57.246
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>The sauna's so relaxing.</i>

56:57.914 --> 56:59.164
<i>Like making love</i>
<i>three times in a row.</i>

56:59.374 --> 57:00.290
<i>WOMAN IN FILM 2:</i>
<i>Oh, my, my.</i>

57:00.500 --> 57:01.750
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>You're so predictable!</i>

57:01.960 --> 57:02.876
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>My poor Christine.</i>

57:03.086 --> 57:04.711
<i>CHRISTINE:</i>
<i>Oh, but such words.</i>

57:05.547 --> 57:06.505
<i>WOMAN IN FILM 2:</i>
<i>You're afraid of words?</i>

57:06.714 --> 57:08.006
<i>CHRISTINE: They're shocking,</i>
<i>that's all.</i>

57:08.550 --> 57:09.591
<i>WOMAN IN FILM 2:</i>
<i>Even after the party?</i>

57:09.801 --> 57:10.843
-[ Christine laughs ]
<i>-Well!</i>

57:11.219 --> 57:13.387
<i>See you in a minute.</i>
<i>Be right with you.</i>

57:14.180 --> 57:16.056
<i>MAN IN FILM: Do you think we</i>
<i>could spend some time together?</i>

57:16.474 --> 57:17.975
You see. Something
to do with you.

57:18.643 --> 57:19.726
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: You mean it?</i>
<i>May I?</i>

57:19.936 --> 57:20.644
<i>MAN IN FILM: It's up to you.</i>

57:20.854 --> 57:22.187
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>I'd like to very much.</i>

57:22.397 --> 57:24.648
<i>MAN: That's perfect.</i>
<i>I invite a drink tonight.</i>

57:24.858 --> 57:26.817
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: It's just that</i>
<i>I'm busy here till rather late.</i>

57:27.026 --> 57:27.818
<i>Till after eight.</i>

57:28.027 --> 57:28.777
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>That will be fine.</i>

57:29.237 --> 57:30.279
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>About 8:30.</i>

57:30.572 --> 57:31.572
<i>-MAN IN FILM: Au revoir.</i>
<i>-WOMAN IN FILM: Au revoir.</i>

57:36.286 --> 57:38.078
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: If only we</i>
<i>were somewhere else.</i>

57:40.457 --> 57:41.748
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>Elsewhere, I know.</i>

57:42.750 --> 57:44.668
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>Dreaming, listening.</i>

57:44.961 --> 57:46.420
<i>Sharing the silence.</i>

57:47.213 --> 57:48.505
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>I like the way you talk.</i>

57:49.132 --> 57:50.591
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>It's my golden vision.</i>

57:51.426 --> 57:52.759
<i>It's not appreciated.</i>

57:53.261 --> 57:54.553
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>It appeals to me.</i>

57:55.680 --> 57:56.638
<i>WOMAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>It's true that I'm naive,</i>

57:56.848 --> 57:59.057
<i>but that's the way I am,</i>
<i>that's all.</i>

58:03.980 --> 58:05.439
<i>MAN IN FILM:</i>
<i>I saw this girl I know, yeah?</i>

58:07.192 --> 58:09.026
<i>WOMAN IN FILM: I feel as if</i>
<i>I've never seen it before.</i>

58:32.884 --> 58:36.512
<i>CHRISTINE: Well, if I decide</i>
<i>to have my sexual relations</i>

58:36.721 --> 58:37.888
<i>before I marry Eric,</i>

58:38.640 --> 58:40.098
<i>I'll do the same</i>
<i>as you, Judith.</i>

58:40.308 --> 58:41.475
<i>It's logical.</i>

58:42.769 --> 58:44.728
<i>JUDITH: We're told to live</i>
<i>with hypocrisy.</i>

58:45.522 --> 58:46.480
<i>We can't applaud truth</i>

58:46.689 --> 58:49.107
<i>and not notice that we are</i>
<i>what we are,</i>

58:49.692 --> 58:51.235
<i>only to despise the truth.</i>

58:51.653 --> 58:55.864
<i>Well, after all that,</i>
<i>what are we looking for?</i>

58:56.783 --> 58:57.783
<i>CHRISTINE: A good question.</i>

58:58.034 --> 59:00.285
<i>JUDITH: Happiness.</i>
<i>Just in our own way.</i>

59:22.850 --> 59:26.186
[ Groaning ]

59:30.650 --> 59:31.650
[ Knocks on door ]

59:31.943 --> 59:33.318
I'm going, Rosie.

59:33.945 --> 59:35.821
I've left you some coffee
on the stove.

59:36.030 --> 59:37.906
Turn it off if you go out, okay?

59:39.826 --> 59:43.161
[ Shivers ]
Okay. Bye.

59:45.039 --> 59:46.832
Are-- aren't you
gonna wish me luck?

59:49.294 --> 59:50.544
Are you okay?

59:50.878 --> 59:53.547
[ Gasping ]
Brushing my teeth.

59:53.756 --> 59:56.550
Uh, bye.

59:57.552 --> 59:59.636
<i>- ROSE: Good luck.</i>
-Thanks.

01:00:01.180 --> 01:00:03.181
<i>-MINDY: See you later!</i>
<i>-[ Groaning ]</i>

01:00:37.216 --> 01:00:39.259
[ Whistle blows ]

01:01:10.291 --> 01:01:11.041
[ Snarls ]

01:01:11.250 --> 01:01:13.251
[ Screaming ]

01:01:42.949 --> 01:01:44.783
Uh, you'll pardon me,
Mr. McLaren,

01:01:44.992 --> 01:01:47.327
but I think the mayor
should be taking this epidemic

01:01:47.537 --> 01:01:48.829
more seriously than he is.

01:01:49.664 --> 01:01:51.873
The city is a complex machine,
Mr. Lapointe.

01:01:52.083 --> 01:01:53.291
It needs constant attention.

01:01:53.793 --> 01:01:56.461
The mayor will listen to you,
but you're not the only one.

01:01:57.004 --> 01:01:58.088
It takes time.

01:01:59.298 --> 01:02:01.133
Clark, why are we stopping?

01:02:01.342 --> 01:02:02.968
CLARK: I am sorry, sir,
but there's no way

01:02:03.177 --> 01:02:04.261
I can get around this truck.

01:02:04.804 --> 01:02:07.264
Isn't there anybody around?
Shall we have to turn around?

01:02:07.473 --> 01:02:08.682
Oh, here's somebody, sir.

01:02:09.434 --> 01:02:10.809
Clark, roll down your window

01:02:11.018 --> 01:02:12.728
and ask them why
the road's blocked.

01:02:12.937 --> 01:02:14.312
Uh, it might be strike trouble.

01:02:14.522 --> 01:02:15.522
-MCLAREN: Be careful.
-CLARK: Yes, sir.

01:02:20.361 --> 01:02:21.319
LAPOINTE:
They've got the disease.

01:02:21.612 --> 01:02:23.280
Look! Their eyes!

01:02:26.451 --> 01:02:27.951
[ Screams ]

01:02:47.430 --> 01:02:48.680
[ Screaming ]

01:02:55.354 --> 01:02:56.480
<i>MAN ON TV: We spoke</i>
<i>with the director</i>

01:02:56.689 --> 01:02:57.856
<i>of the</i>
<i>World Health Organization,</i>

01:02:58.065 --> 01:02:59.524
<i>who had just arrived</i>
<i>from England</i>

01:02:59.734 --> 01:03:00.859
<i>to take charge of liaison</i>

01:03:01.068 --> 01:03:03.653
<i>with health bureaus</i>
<i>in Western European countries.</i>

01:03:08.075 --> 01:03:09.826
Dr. Gentry, do you honestly feel

01:03:10.036 --> 01:03:12.162
that this is a time
for martial law?

01:03:13.581 --> 01:03:14.956
I don't think there is
any question

01:03:15.166 --> 01:03:16.750
that martial law is needed

01:03:16.959 --> 01:03:19.085
in the city of Montreal
at this point in time.

01:03:19.545 --> 01:03:20.378
It's a necessity.

01:03:21.255 --> 01:03:22.714
It has already been established

01:03:22.924 --> 01:03:24.508
that the victims
of the disease--

01:03:24.717 --> 01:03:25.842
and it is not rabies,

01:03:26.052 --> 01:03:28.261
though it may be related
to the rabies virus--

01:03:28.679 --> 01:03:31.431
that the victims of the disease
are beyond medical help,

01:03:31.641 --> 01:03:34.142
once it has established itself
to the degree

01:03:34.352 --> 01:03:36.269
of inducing violent behavior.

01:03:36.813 --> 01:03:38.063
What you're saying, then, sir,

01:03:38.272 --> 01:03:40.398
that is if these people have
contracted the disease,

01:03:40.608 --> 01:03:41.274
that there isn't...

01:03:41.484 --> 01:03:43.652
What I am saying is very simple,

01:03:44.070 --> 01:03:46.363
and it may not be very palatable
for your viewers.

01:03:47.949 --> 01:03:50.659
Shooting down the victims
is as good a way

01:03:50.868 --> 01:03:52.869
of handling them
as we have got.

01:03:53.371 --> 01:03:54.287
If we lock them up,

01:03:54.497 --> 01:03:58.583
they eventually go into a coma
and die shortly afterwards.

01:03:59.085 --> 01:04:00.502
<i>We have got a vaccine</i>

01:04:00.962 --> 01:04:03.088
<i>that we think will work</i>
<i>in a preventative way,</i>

01:04:03.798 --> 01:04:07.050
<i>but for those that are already</i>
<i>incubating the disease...</i>

01:04:07.260 --> 01:04:08.718
-Come on, Murray.
-I'm coming.

01:04:08.928 --> 01:04:09.761
Rose is waiting for me.

01:04:09.971 --> 01:04:11.638
Well, don't get pushy.
We're going.

01:04:11.848 --> 01:04:13.765
<i>Dr. Gentry,</i>
<i>these are very serious...</i>

01:04:14.058 --> 01:04:15.851
-Bye-bye, Murray.
-I'll see ya.

01:04:16.143 --> 01:04:18.603
<i>All those receiving shots</i>
<i>of the new vaccine</i>

01:04:18.813 --> 01:04:21.690
<i>are being issued</i>
<i>these plastic identity cards.</i>

01:04:22.441 --> 01:04:25.026
<i>Viewers are urged</i>
<i>not to leave their homes</i>

01:04:25.236 --> 01:04:26.862
<i>unless absolutely necessary,</i>

01:04:27.113 --> 01:04:28.697
<i>and are reminded</i>
<i>that if they do,</i>

01:04:28.906 --> 01:04:31.116
<i>they must carry their</i>
<i>vaccine cards with them.</i>

01:04:31.450 --> 01:04:33.326
<i>Police, army,</i>
<i>and militia officers</i>

01:04:33.536 --> 01:04:34.870
<i>may demand to see them.</i>

01:04:37.582 --> 01:04:38.665
You got the keys?

01:04:38.875 --> 01:04:39.666
Oh.

01:04:40.209 --> 01:04:41.543
Remember to keep
your windows up

01:04:41.752 --> 01:04:44.129
and your doors locked
once you get into the city.

01:04:44.338 --> 01:04:45.755
Maybe the bug can't get you now,

01:04:45.965 --> 01:04:48.091
but that shot won't protect you
from the crazies.

01:04:48.426 --> 01:04:49.676
-Take care.
-Thanks a lot.

01:04:49.886 --> 01:04:51.803
-All right, take care.
-Okay.

01:04:52.930 --> 01:04:54.055
You got enough room.

01:04:54.932 --> 01:04:56.266
-All right there?
-Yeah.

01:04:57.935 --> 01:04:59.060
[ Engine starting ]

01:05:00.897 --> 01:05:02.939
[ Sirens wailing ]

01:05:16.704 --> 01:05:17.412
[ Sighs ]

01:06:22.687 --> 01:06:23.687
Hi.

01:06:25.731 --> 01:06:26.982
Mind if I sit down?

01:06:28.234 --> 01:06:29.359
I don't mind.

01:06:40.121 --> 01:06:41.705
Sure is nice, eh, Christmas?

01:06:49.338 --> 01:06:50.463
Uh, do you smoke?

01:06:51.841 --> 01:06:52.632
Cigarettes?

01:06:55.678 --> 01:06:57.679
-Huh?
-Do you want a cigarette?

01:07:10.609 --> 01:07:12.777
Oh, have you got a light?

01:07:15.823 --> 01:07:16.781
A lighter?

01:07:22.288 --> 01:07:24.831
Oh! I'll get a light
from that guy over there, okay?

01:07:26.751 --> 01:07:27.751
I'll be right back.

01:07:33.507 --> 01:07:34.632
You got a light, buddy?

01:07:35.509 --> 01:07:37.594
[ Growls ]

01:07:37.803 --> 01:07:39.637
[ Screams ]

01:07:42.641 --> 01:07:44.893
OFFICER: Stop!
Stop or I'll shoot!

01:07:46.312 --> 01:07:48.188
Stop! Stop him.

01:07:49.648 --> 01:07:50.732
Get out of the way!

01:07:52.026 --> 01:07:52.817
Stop!

01:07:54.153 --> 01:07:55.153
-[ Gunfire ]
-[ Groaning ]

01:07:56.530 --> 01:07:57.989
[ Screaming ]

01:08:01.702 --> 01:08:03.495
[ Groans ]

01:08:03.704 --> 01:08:05.705
[ Screaming ]

01:08:11.128 --> 01:08:12.253
Christ.

01:08:12.963 --> 01:08:15.673
Rose? Are you home?

01:08:16.300 --> 01:08:17.634
Well, you'll never guess
what happened to me

01:08:17.843 --> 01:08:18.801
on the subway today.

01:08:19.220 --> 01:08:20.886
Well, the whole city's
gone crazy.

01:08:21.096 --> 01:08:23.305
[ Gasping ]

01:08:26.477 --> 01:08:27.519
Aww.

01:08:28.645 --> 01:08:30.270
Have you been out?

01:08:31.232 --> 01:08:32.439
Have you gotten your shot?

01:08:33.943 --> 01:08:35.193
Oh...

01:08:36.194 --> 01:08:37.529
I can't go out.

01:08:38.863 --> 01:08:40.948
I can't go out.
[ Sobs ]

01:08:44.662 --> 01:08:46.996
-What's been going on?
-Oh!

01:08:47.247 --> 01:08:48.997
What's the matter with you?

01:08:52.002 --> 01:08:53.711
-You poor kid.
-[ Sobs ]

01:08:55.464 --> 01:08:57.631
Well, don't you worry.

01:08:58.716 --> 01:09:01.261
I'm here, and I'm
gonna take care of you.

01:09:04.390 --> 01:09:06.558
<i>MAN ON RADIO: And the crisis</i>
<i>has now been officially granted</i>

01:09:06.767 --> 01:09:10.060
<i>epidemic status by officials of</i>
<i>the World Health Organization.</i>

01:09:10.563 --> 01:09:11.688
<i>The Prime Minister</i>
<i>was reluctant</i>

01:09:11.897 --> 01:09:14.189
<i>to officially declare</i>
<i>a state of emergency,</i>

01:09:14.483 --> 01:09:16.526
<i>but, as any citizen</i>
<i>in the streets can tell you,</i>

01:09:16.777 --> 01:09:19.154
<i>martial law has</i>
<i>come to Montreal.</i>

01:09:24.702 --> 01:09:26.911
[ People chattering ]

01:09:27.287 --> 01:09:29.372
[ Baby crying ]

01:09:36.881 --> 01:09:38.046
Okay, fine.

01:09:40.009 --> 01:09:41.634
I'm sorry you don't have an...
Where's your ID card?

01:09:42.011 --> 01:09:44.011
Uh, would you mind standing
over in front, please?

01:09:46.140 --> 01:09:47.974
-Can I get through?
-Thanks.

01:09:50.185 --> 01:09:52.395
...an emergency and you've
got to attend, or...

01:09:52.938 --> 01:09:54.564
Right at the back.
It's only three minutes.

01:09:55.024 --> 01:09:56.774
It'll be all over
before you know it.

01:09:57.026 --> 01:09:59.235
Get the shot, okay?
Thank you very much.

01:09:59.445 --> 01:10:01.321
<i>-At the back.</i>
<i>-WOMAN: Thank you.</i>

01:10:01.572 --> 01:10:02.488
Sorry. You don't have
an ID card,

01:10:02.698 --> 01:10:03.489
you can't go through there.

01:10:03.699 --> 01:10:05.116
Would you mind standing
over that way, please?

01:10:05.367 --> 01:10:06.534
Uh, get that guy.

01:10:07.244 --> 01:10:08.286
I'm sorry, sir,
you can't get through.

01:10:09.038 --> 01:10:09.746
I'm sorry, sir...

01:10:09.955 --> 01:10:10.705
Leave him alone.
Don't push him.

01:10:10.956 --> 01:10:13.249
-You don't have a card. Now...
-You've got no right to do that.

01:10:28.140 --> 01:10:30.892
Uh... How long are we
gonna be stuck here?

01:11:00.881 --> 01:11:02.465
I can't believe this.

01:11:03.217 --> 01:11:04.425
It's like we're at war.

01:11:05.427 --> 01:11:06.302
Listen, Hart.

01:11:07.388 --> 01:11:08.888
I want to go to my place first.

01:11:09.682 --> 01:11:11.140
I just won't be comfortable

01:11:11.350 --> 01:11:12.767
till I know everything
is okay back there.

01:11:13.727 --> 01:11:15.770
Now, when we get there, I'll
give you the keys to the car,

01:11:15.980 --> 01:11:17.146
and you can pick up your girl,
okay?

01:11:17.481 --> 01:11:18.564
Yeah, okay.

01:11:50.389 --> 01:11:52.432
[ Siren wails ]

01:11:56.020 --> 01:11:59.564
Listen, uh, phone me
when you get there, eh?

01:12:00.190 --> 01:12:01.232
Yeah, okay.

01:12:04.320 --> 01:12:05.194
Hey.

01:12:09.199 --> 01:12:12.368
Look, uh, maybe it would be
a good idea if you--

01:12:12.703 --> 01:12:13.911
if you bring Rosie back
with you.

01:12:14.121 --> 01:12:16.080
You know, just till this thing
blows over.

01:12:18.709 --> 01:12:20.209
Yeah, okay.

01:12:22.212 --> 01:12:24.339
-Listen, Murray.
-Yeah?

01:12:27.092 --> 01:12:28.718
Thanks for the car, all right?

01:12:30.346 --> 01:12:31.971
Keep the windows shut
and lock the door.

01:12:32.389 --> 01:12:34.640
-All right.
-I'll see you soon.

01:12:34.850 --> 01:12:35.850
I'll call ya.

01:12:51.700 --> 01:12:52.617
'Cile?

01:13:07.049 --> 01:13:08.800
Hey, Cecile, I'm home.

01:13:11.678 --> 01:13:12.637
Honey?

01:13:14.932 --> 01:13:16.224
Sweetie, I'm home.

01:13:16.475 --> 01:13:17.266
[ Sighs ]

01:13:17.684 --> 01:13:19.018
Hey, Cecile?

01:13:20.104 --> 01:13:21.396
Hey, sweetie.

01:13:25.067 --> 01:13:25.858
Honey?

01:13:30.572 --> 01:13:32.031
'Cile?

01:13:37.663 --> 01:13:38.454
Sweetie?

01:13:41.458 --> 01:13:42.583
Sweetie, I'm home.

01:13:57.307 --> 01:13:59.350
[ Rattling sounds ]

01:14:03.564 --> 01:14:04.772
'Cile?

01:14:14.616 --> 01:14:15.408
Honey?

01:14:47.024 --> 01:14:48.274
[ Gasps ]

01:14:55.324 --> 01:14:56.491
Oh, God.

01:15:14.510 --> 01:15:15.718
[ Sobs ]

01:15:16.929 --> 01:15:18.221
Oh...

01:15:23.602 --> 01:15:24.727
[ Woman whimpering ]

01:15:32.611 --> 01:15:34.612
[ Screeches ]

01:15:35.322 --> 01:15:36.072
Get off me!

01:15:45.666 --> 01:15:46.958
That's it, Rosie.

01:15:48.460 --> 01:15:50.878
You just get as much sleep
as you need.

01:15:59.638 --> 01:16:01.514
Don't think about anything.

01:16:06.353 --> 01:16:08.688
Just let your mind drift.

01:16:20.576 --> 01:16:22.159
<i>GENTRY ON TV: So after using</i>
<i>some rather elaborate</i>

01:16:22.369 --> 01:16:23.911
<i>tracking procedures,</i>

01:16:24.121 --> 01:16:25.496
<i>and applying them to a map,</i>

01:16:25.706 --> 01:16:27.623
<i>we find that the disease</i>
<i>does in fact seem to have</i>

01:16:27.833 --> 01:16:29.584
<i>a very specific</i>
<i>place of origin.</i>

01:16:29.793 --> 01:16:30.501
<i>INTERVIEWER: Which is?</i>

01:16:30.711 --> 01:16:31.544
<i>GENTRY: Which is...</i>

01:16:31.837 --> 01:16:33.838
<i>the Keloid Clinic</i>
<i>of Cosmetic Surgery,</i>

01:16:34.256 --> 01:16:36.173
<i>a few miles outside</i>
<i>the town of Camelford.</i>

01:16:37.217 --> 01:16:38.884
<i>You can see</i>
<i>with your own eyes</i>

01:16:39.094 --> 01:16:40.803
<i>how everything has</i>
<i>spread out from there</i>

01:16:41.013 --> 01:16:43.222
<i>in geometrically</i>
<i>increasing proportions.</i>

01:16:44.433 --> 01:16:45.349
<i>Now, this pattern,</i>

01:16:45.559 --> 01:16:48.144
<i>in conjunction with</i>
<i>some of our own statistics,</i>

01:16:48.729 --> 01:16:50.980
<i>indicates that there is</i>
<i>a strong possibility</i>

01:16:51.440 --> 01:16:52.607
<i>there is a special factor</i>
<i>at work</i>

01:16:52.816 --> 01:16:53.899
<i>in the spread of the disease.</i>

01:16:54.192 --> 01:16:55.610
<i>INTERVIEWER:</i>
<i>You mean a carrier?</i>

01:16:56.069 --> 01:16:57.945
<i>GENTRY: Well, at the risk</i>
<i>of setting off</i>

01:16:58.155 --> 01:16:59.947
<i>a futile witch hunt, yes.</i>

01:17:00.907 --> 01:17:03.534
<i>Someone like</i>
<i>the infamous Typhoid Mary,</i>

01:17:03.744 --> 01:17:05.870
<i>who incubates the disease</i>
<i>and transmits it,</i>

01:17:06.330 --> 01:17:08.122
<i>but is herself immune to it.</i>

01:17:08.582 --> 01:17:09.749
<i>INTERVIEWER: Well,</i>
<i>what were they doing</i>

01:17:09.958 --> 01:17:11.959
<i>at the Keloid Clinic, then,</i>
<i>Dr. Gentry?</i>

01:17:29.186 --> 01:17:30.936
[ Tires screech ]

01:17:58.674 --> 01:18:00.216
[ Snarling ]

01:18:08.934 --> 01:18:10.393
-[ Gunshot ]
-[ Groans ]

01:18:11.937 --> 01:18:13.270
[ Gunshot ]

01:18:15.649 --> 01:18:17.233
Okay, Jack, that's another.

01:19:35.771 --> 01:19:38.147
Oh, no! Rose!

01:19:38.899 --> 01:19:42.193
Well, you-- you can't!
It's dangerous out there!

01:19:42.402 --> 01:19:44.862
Mindy, I don't want it
to be you.

01:19:45.071 --> 01:19:47.823
Well, of-- of course
it should be me.

01:19:48.450 --> 01:19:50.868
But-- who else
but your best friend?

01:19:51.328 --> 01:19:52.828
I'll take care of you.

01:19:53.038 --> 01:19:55.164
Oh, I ache all over.

01:19:55.957 --> 01:19:58.042
I hurt from the inside out.

01:19:58.794 --> 01:20:01.587
Well-- well, then--
then, what you need is--

01:20:01.797 --> 01:20:04.298
is a nice, hot bath.

01:20:04.549 --> 01:20:05.925
It'll relax you and--

01:20:06.134 --> 01:20:08.219
and then you won't ache
anymore.

01:20:08.470 --> 01:20:09.261
Mm.

01:20:19.856 --> 01:20:21.899
[ Sirens wailing ]

01:20:51.513 --> 01:20:52.346
[ Gasps ]

01:21:08.238 --> 01:21:09.947
It's not my fault.

01:21:14.619 --> 01:21:15.953
It's you.

01:21:23.169 --> 01:21:24.670
It's been you all along.

01:21:25.255 --> 01:21:26.797
What are you talking about?

01:21:30.510 --> 01:21:32.052
You carry the plague.

01:21:32.262 --> 01:21:33.971
You've killed hundreds
of people!

01:21:36.349 --> 01:21:38.225
You don't know
what you're talking about!

01:21:38.602 --> 01:21:40.019
I'm still me.

01:21:41.563 --> 01:21:42.688
I'm still Rose.

01:21:42.898 --> 01:21:45.024
You're still Rose?
You're not Rose!

01:21:47.235 --> 01:21:48.861
What did they do to ya
at that clinic, eh?

01:21:49.070 --> 01:21:49.778
Ah!

01:21:49.988 --> 01:21:51.739
-What did they turn you into?
-[ Whimpering ]

01:21:52.073 --> 01:21:54.116
I have to have blood.

01:21:55.201 --> 01:21:57.369
It's all I can eat.

01:21:58.788 --> 01:22:00.372
And it's not my fault.

01:22:01.082 --> 01:22:02.750
[ Screaming ]
It's your fault!

01:22:03.043 --> 01:22:04.835
It's all your fault!

01:22:05.045 --> 01:22:06.337
Rose, stop!

01:22:06.546 --> 01:22:07.546
[ Screams ]
God!

01:22:08.089 --> 01:22:08.964
[ Screams ]

01:22:09.174 --> 01:22:10.174
Oh, Rose...

01:22:10.467 --> 01:22:11.550
[ Sobs ]

01:22:11.885 --> 01:22:14.637
Rose, there must be
a way to fix this.

01:22:14.846 --> 01:22:16.972
Look, we'll go to the police.

01:22:17.974 --> 01:22:18.766
No.

01:22:18.975 --> 01:22:20.893
Rose.
We'll go to the hospital.

01:22:21.353 --> 01:22:24.063
Oh, it won't work.
Now, just leave me alone!

01:22:24.272 --> 01:22:26.148
-Rose! Come here.
-No!

01:22:26.358 --> 01:22:28.609
-I'm sorry! Come here, wait!
-Let me go!

01:22:28.818 --> 01:22:29.985
-Rose!
-Let me go!

01:22:30.195 --> 01:22:30.986
No, no!

01:22:31.196 --> 01:22:33.572
Listen, Rose. Listen.
Listen. Listen to me.

01:22:33.865 --> 01:22:35.491
-Listen to me, you're right.
-No.

01:22:35.700 --> 01:22:37.284
You're right.
We're in it together.

01:22:37.827 --> 01:22:39.370
-We'll figure it out together.
-Ah!

01:22:39.955 --> 01:22:41.789
-[ Groans ]
-[ Screams ]

01:22:42.499 --> 01:22:43.415
-[ Grunts ]
-[ Metallic clang ]

01:22:48.004 --> 01:22:48.837
[ Sighs ]

01:23:48.732 --> 01:23:50.774
[ Panting ]

01:23:53.069 --> 01:23:53.944
[ Sighs ]

01:24:02.370 --> 01:24:04.413
[ Siren wails ]

01:24:10.670 --> 01:24:11.712
Oh...

01:24:13.173 --> 01:24:14.006
Hi.

01:24:15.300 --> 01:24:17.259
I've seen you
around here before, haven't I?

01:24:18.511 --> 01:24:20.596
Um, I used to live
in this building,

01:24:20.805 --> 01:24:23.015
and, uh, they still deliver
my mail here.

01:24:25.769 --> 01:24:27.728
I'm a-- a friend
of Mindy Kent's.

01:24:28.855 --> 01:24:30.230
I was supposed
to meet her here,

01:24:30.440 --> 01:24:32.649
but, um, she must have
gone out.

01:24:33.276 --> 01:24:34.902
[ Telephone rings ]

01:24:35.570 --> 01:24:36.570
[ Groans ]

01:24:45.163 --> 01:24:46.163
[ Sighs ]

01:25:01.763 --> 01:25:03.764
[ Groans ]

01:25:06.059 --> 01:25:08.102
[ Sighs ]

01:25:17.403 --> 01:25:18.821
[ Ringing continues ]

01:25:26.204 --> 01:25:27.037
[ Sighs ]

01:25:28.998 --> 01:25:30.791
[ Panting ]

01:25:31.501 --> 01:25:32.918
-Hello?
-<i>ROSE: Hart.</i>

01:25:33.878 --> 01:25:35.170
It's me.

01:25:36.005 --> 01:25:38.590
Oh, I'm so glad I finally
managed to get you.

01:25:38.800 --> 01:25:40.050
Rose, where are ya?

01:25:40.552 --> 01:25:42.010
Are you all right?

01:25:43.012 --> 01:25:44.221
Did I hurt you?

01:25:44.764 --> 01:25:47.516
Listen, we should be together.
Please, tell me where you are.

01:25:48.601 --> 01:25:51.353
Well, what you said hurt me.

01:25:52.564 --> 01:25:54.022
It scared me.

01:25:55.316 --> 01:25:57.234
It-- it scared me because I--

01:25:57.443 --> 01:25:59.695
I suddenly realized
you might be right.

01:26:01.698 --> 01:26:05.534
If you are right
about my being a carrier,

01:26:06.536 --> 01:26:07.703
I mean, uh...

01:26:08.621 --> 01:26:10.372
I murdered Mindy.

01:26:10.957 --> 01:26:12.457
I murdered a lot of people.

01:26:13.001 --> 01:26:13.792
Rose.

01:26:14.627 --> 01:26:15.669
There's no reason--

01:26:15.879 --> 01:26:18.172
So I decided
to try a little experiment,

01:26:18.715 --> 01:26:20.966
just to prove that you
were wrong about all that.

01:26:21.718 --> 01:26:25.053
You see? I'm being positive,
aren't I?

01:26:25.972 --> 01:26:29.892
So I found myself a partner
for my little experiment,

01:26:32.812 --> 01:26:35.022
a real normal, healthy guy,

01:26:36.191 --> 01:26:39.193
and I took some blood,
just a bit.

01:26:41.029 --> 01:26:43.280
And I've locked myself
in a room with him.

01:26:45.366 --> 01:26:48.744
And I'm gonna stay here until I
make sure he doesn't get sick.

01:26:51.289 --> 01:26:52.664
And then I'll know...

01:26:54.292 --> 01:26:56.335
I'm not the one
who started it all.

01:26:57.003 --> 01:26:58.128
Rose, look.

01:26:59.088 --> 01:27:01.048
You gotta get out of there.
Right away.

01:27:02.175 --> 01:27:04.593
You're committing suicide.
You know that?

01:27:05.386 --> 01:27:09.932
Listen, can't we just
be together over the phone?

01:27:10.266 --> 01:27:12.976
I mean, just for a little while.
Just--

01:27:13.728 --> 01:27:15.062
just until I find out.

01:27:15.647 --> 01:27:18.482
I mean, we can be together
on the phone

01:27:18.816 --> 01:27:20.192
just for a while, can't we?

01:27:20.401 --> 01:27:21.652
[ Sobs ]

01:27:21.861 --> 01:27:22.569
[ Sighs ]

01:27:22.779 --> 01:27:25.405
Oh, Hart.
Please. Listen.

01:27:25.782 --> 01:27:28.617
Please, no.

01:27:28.952 --> 01:27:30.953
Rose, get out of there!

01:27:32.205 --> 01:27:35.457
<i>Look, just get up</i>
<i>and drop the phone</i>

01:27:35.667 --> 01:27:37.542
<i>and walk out the door</i>

01:27:37.919 --> 01:27:40.003
and run out of there
as fast as you can.

01:27:41.256 --> 01:27:42.798
<i>You're not giving us</i>
<i>enough time.</i>

01:27:43.007 --> 01:27:43.632
<i>You're not giving</i>
<i>either of us--</i>

01:27:44.259 --> 01:27:45.550
Oh, Hart. No, don't.

01:27:45.760 --> 01:27:49.304
-Listen. I can't. Hart.
<i>-Rose... [ Sobbing ]</i>

01:27:50.265 --> 01:27:51.306
Hart...

01:27:51.975 --> 01:27:52.808
[ Sobbing ]
Rose!

01:27:53.393 --> 01:27:55.394
-Hart?
<i>-Rose, get out of there!</i>

01:27:55.603 --> 01:27:57.938
-I'm afraid!
-Get out of there!

01:27:58.356 --> 01:27:59.982
Hart...

01:28:00.191 --> 01:28:01.233
[ Screams ]

01:28:01.943 --> 01:28:05.028
No! No!

01:28:05.655 --> 01:28:07.698
No!
[ Screams ]

01:28:08.449 --> 01:28:09.241
No!

01:28:10.201 --> 01:28:11.910
[ Sobbing ]

01:28:13.037 --> 01:28:14.538
No, no!

01:28:15.081 --> 01:28:15.914
No!

01:28:16.332 --> 01:28:17.082
No!

01:28:17.834 --> 01:28:20.002
[ Siren wailing ]

01:28:21.212 --> 01:28:23.046
[ Gunshot ]

